Chapter-1 : IAC Code Generation with AI - From Zero to vibe coding :
====================================================================
  Module Intro  :
  ---------------
    This is the very first module on how we can build our right infrastructure as a code using AI. 
    and this is the module we're going to help build the in a coceptual foundation and also help you get from zero to web coding your way using the AI tools like Copilot and VS code and so on.

  Learning Objectives : 
  =====================
   Let's look at what are the learning objective for this module :
    > Understand AI-Driven Infrastructure as Code fundamentals : Use AI to generate infrastructure code instead of writing Terraform manually.
    > Master the differnce between vibe and spec workflow      : Vibe is fast AI-assisted coding; Spec is slow, detailed, manual coding. 
    > Set up vsc with GitHub Copilot & cursor                  : Set up AI tools in VS Code to auto-suggest, generate, and explain Terraform code.
    > Generate terraform code fro aws using vibe coding        : Describe AWS resources in English and let AI create Terraform code.
    > Complete mini project: Provision Ec2 with AI assistance  : Provision an EC2 instance using AI-generated Terraform as hands-on practice.
Explanation in simple :
-----------------------
  In this module, we will first build a strong basic understanding of what AI-driven or AI-assisted Infrastructure as Code really means.
  We will start by learning the traditional way of writing infrastructure code, and then compare it with vibe coding, where we use AI to help us write code faster and easier.
  We will understand how AI helps in writing code, and also get introduced to spec-based workflows, which are more structured and used for production environments.
  We will not go very deep into spec workflows now, but we will clearly understand the concepts, which we will use later in the course.
  Next, we will set up our working environment, because this module includes a hands-on project.
  The environment will be created in a way that everyone can follow, without spending money.
  We will mainly use VS Code, which is free and open source, and available to everyone.
  We will also use GitHub Copilot, an AI assistant that works inside VS Code. We can use it with a free personal GitHub account, so no paid tools are required.
  Even though tools like Cursor exist and are paid, we will focus on free tools first, so everyone can learn comfortably.
  For the project, we will provision an EC2 instance using AI assistance.
  We will use an AWS free tier account, so we don’t have to worry about infrastructure costs.

